President Barack Obama issued a statement on Haitian Flag Day, congratulating those who celebrate the occasion. He highlighted the historical connection between Haiti and the United States, referencing how freedmen from Haiti assisted American patriots during the Siege of Savannah in 200 years ago. He also acknowledged Haiti's declaration of independence in 1803 and the significance of the first Haitian flag. While celebrating this day, he urged people to remember the ongoing efforts in Haiti to rebuild and recover from the devastating earthquake. He expressed solidarity with the international community in supporting the Haitian government and people in their pursuit of a brighter future. The President assured Haiti that they have a friend and partner in America.